-- Sanyo to Boost Solar Panel Production Capacity at Shiga, Osaka Plants
-- Mariko Yasu
-- 2010-06-15T04:50:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/sanyo-to-boost-solar-panel-production-capacity-at-shiga-osaka-plants.html

          
          
             Sanyo Electric Co. plans to boost
production capacity at solar plants in Osaka and Shiga
prefecture, the company said in a statement today in Tokyo.  
 The Osaka plant will increase solar-cell output to 345
megawatts annually from 210 megawatts by March 2011, Sanyo said.
The company will also increase production capacity of a solar-
module plant in Shiga, western Japan, to 250 megawatts from 100
megawatts by March 2011, according to the statement.  
